    "Name": "Bradford IFV",
    "Details": "The M2A1 revision builds on the upgrades of the M2A, replacing the 140-rated engine with a more powerful 205. These changes pack another 5 tons onto the vehicle's frame, which is slightly offset by an upgrade to ferrofiborous armor. The Bradford Infantry Fighting Vehicle is designed to stay with it's dismounted troops and enter the fight. The heavy punch of the TBM-15 missile system serves as a deterrent to armored threats, at least in theory.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Biome Restrictions: None.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 5/8 hexes / 150/240 meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       125     25\n<b>Left</b>         110     25\n<b>Right</b>       110     25\n<b>Rear</b>        100     25\n<b>Turret</b>      115     25\n\n<b>Total</b>      560    125</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - Missiles</color>\n\n<color=#ffcc00> Can carry 1 Battle Armor Squads. Has firing ports.</color>",
